#. Tag: para
#: hacking.docbook:62
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For every field in the collection, an <markup>&lt;entry&gt;</markup> may "
"contain an element whose name is identical to the field name. If multiple "
"values are allowed for the field, then the letter <emphasis>s</emphasis> is "
"added to the field name to create an element, and each value is added as a "
"child of the element, as in the case of the author, genre, and keyword "
"fields above."
msgstr ""
"Za vsako polje v zbirki lahko <markup>&lt;entry&gt;</markup> vsebuje "
"element, katerega ime je enako imenu polja. Če je za polje dovoljenih več "
"vrednosti, je črka <emphasis>s</emphasis> dodana imenu polja, da se ustvari "
"element, in vsaka vrednost je dodana kot podrejena elementu, kot v primeru "
"avtorja, zvrst in polja za ključne besede zgoraj."

#. Tag: para
#: hacking.docbook:66
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"As a result, if additional fields are added to the collection, the data file "
"will no longer conform to the DTD. However, &appname; uses a non-validating "
"&XML; parser, so additional fields do not cause problems."
msgstr ""
"Posledično, če so zbirki dodana dodatna polja, podatkovna datoteka ne bo več "
"v skladu z DTD. Vendar &appname; uporablja nepreverjalni &XML; "
"razčlenjevalnik, tako da dodatna polja ne povzročajo težav."

#. Tag: title
#: hacking.docbook:72
#, no-c-format
msgid "Images"
msgstr "Slike"

#. Tag: programlisting
#: hacking.docbook:73
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<![CDATA[\n"
"  <images>\n"
"   <image width=\"111\" format=\"JPEG\" height=\"140\" id="
"\"cf65a2f023b6cb9e9233323dca10ac7c.jpeg\" />\n"
"  </images>\n"
"]]>"
msgstr ""
"<![CDATA[\n"
"  <images>\n"
"   <image width=\"111\" format=\"JPEG\" height=\"140\" id="
"\"cf65a2f023b6cb9e9233323dca10ac7c.jpeg\" />\n"
"  </images>\n"
"]]>"

#. Tag: para
#: hacking.docbook:75
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Inside the <markup>&lt;images&gt;</markup> element, each image referenced by "
"an entry is listed, along with attributes describing the image's size, "
"format, and id. If the image is contained inside the Zip file, the element "
"is empty. Otherwise, the image data may be contained in the &XML; stream as "
"base64-encoded text."
msgstr ""
"Znotraj elementa <markup>&lt;images&gt;</markup> je navedena vsaka slika, na "
"katero se sklicuje vnos, skupaj z atributi, ki opisujejo velikost, obliko in "
"ID slike. Če je slika v datoteki Zip, je element prazen. V nasprotnem "
"primeru so lahko slikovni podatki v datoteki &XML; tok kot besedilo, "
"kodirano z base64."

